description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/rpl/messages.c:347-356

The option iterator init function checks for NULL `it` but allows NULL `data` with non-zero `len`:

```c
void lichen_rpl_opt_iter_init(struct lichen_rpl_opt_iter *it,
                              const uint8_t *data, size_t len)
{
    if (it == NULL) {
        return;
    }
    it->data = data;  // Can be NULL
    it->len = len;    // Can be non-zero
    ...
}
```

While `lichen_rpl_opt_iter_next` does check for this condition and returns INVALID, it would be cleaner to reject invalid input at init time.

Impact: Deferred error detection, inconsistent with defensive programming pattern.

Suggested fix: Clear len to 0 if data is NULL, or return error status.
